# Cursor rules (thin wrapper)
#
# Canonical agent protocol lives in `AGENTS.md`. Keep this file short to avoid
# duplicated/contradicting instructions across agents and IDEs.

## Always use BRAINDRAIN first

- For discovery: call `search_tools(query, top_k=...)` before any repo-wide search or large file reads.
- For big outputs: call `route_output(text, source, intent=...)` instead of pasting raw logs/diffs/JSON into chat.
- For retrieval: use `search_index(query, limit=...)` (or `ctx_search` on context-mode) to pull only relevant chunks.
- For measurement: call `get_token_dashboard()` at milestones to confirm savings.

## Fallback policy

Only fall back to native file reads/grep/glob when:
- `search_tools()` can’t find a suitable MCP tool, or
- the task is tiny and local (single small file / small diff).
